HEADWORD: Septuagesimal
<hw>Sep`tu*a*ges"i*mal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Consisting
of seventy days, years, etc.; reckoned by seventies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our abridged and <qex>septuagesimal</qex> age.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Septuagint</ent>⟦br⟧
